  "commentary": "With SPX at 6606.59 sitting just above the massive +122.7B gamma wall at 6600 and well above the 6596 flip strike, dealers are in full sell-the-rally mode as they hedge their long gamma positions by selling into strength. The PIN regime with this heavy positive gamma concentration from 6600-6620 creates a strong magnetic pull back toward 6600, especially given the 36-54% GEX surge indicating fresh options flow amplifying dealer hedging needs. Key resistance sits at 6610 (+80.8B) and 6620 (+54.9B) where dealer selling pressure intensifies, while any dip toward 6600 triggers dealer buying support.\n\nBottom line: expect price to get pulled back down toward 6600 with resistance at higher strikes.",
